<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Myoporum</i> <i>laetum</i>, <i>Schinus</i> <i>molle</i> or <i>Schinus</i> <i>terebinthifolius</i> is dominant in the tree canopy . </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text"> Trees < 18 m tall; canopy is open to continuous. Shrubs are infrequent or common. Herbaceous layer is simple to diverse. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Schinus molle</i> > 80% relative cover in the tree layer (cf. Keeler-Wolf and Evens 2006). <i>M. laetum</i> or <i>S. molle</i> > 60% relative cover in the tree layer (Stillwater Sciences and URS 2007).</li>
		
		<li><i>Myoporum laetum</i> > 50% relative cover in the tree layer (Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Coastal canyons, washes, slopes, riparian areas, roadsides.  </div>
</div>

        
